2363
03:12:06,375 --> 03:12:07,875
Good evening.

2364
03:12:17,833 --> 03:12:23,167
My uncle is, above all,
a principled artist.

2365
03:12:25,708 --> 03:12:30,625
His lifelong ambition was not
only to define an epoch,

2366
03:12:30,708 --> 03:12:32,875
but to transcend all time.

2367
03:12:34,333 --> 03:12:38,792
In his memoirs, he described
his designs as machines

2368
03:12:38,875 --> 03:12:41,125
with no superfluous parts.

2369
03:12:41,208 --> 03:12:46,167
That, at their best,
at his best,

2370
03:12:47,500 --> 03:12:50,417
possessed an immoveable core,

2371
03:12:50,500 --> 03:12:52,375
a hard core of beauty.

2372
03:12:53,458 --> 03:12:57,625
<i>A way of directing their
inhabitants' perception</i>

2373
03:12:57,708 --> 03:12:59,875
<i>into the world as it is.</i>

2374
03:12:59,958 --> 03:13:02,708
<i>The inherent laws
of concrete things</i>

2375
03:13:02,792 --> 03:13:06,625
<i>such as mountains
and rock define them.</i>

2376
03:13:06,708 --> 03:13:09,125
<i>They indicate nothing.</i>

2377
03:13:09,208 --> 03:13:11,000
<i>They tell nothing.</i>

2378
03:13:11,083 --> 03:13:12,833
<i>They simply are.</i>

2379
03:13:12,917 --> 03:13:14,875
<i>Born in 1911</i>

2380
03:13:14,958 --> 03:13:17,583
<i>in a small fishing village
in Austria-Hungary,</i>

2381
03:13:17,667 --> 03:13:20,958
<i>László Tóth looked out
upon the Adriatic Sea.</i>

2382
03:13:21,042 --> 03:13:24,917
<i>He was a boy with eyes
wide open, full of yearning.</i>

2383
03:13:25,000 --> 03:13:26,667
<i>New borders would eventually</i>

2384
03:13:26,750 --> 03:13:29,917
<i>rip this expanse of sea
away from him,</i>

2385
03:13:30,000 --> 03:13:34,167
<i>but never did he stop
to try and fill its void.</i>

2386
03:13:34,250 --> 03:13:37,667
<i>Forty years later, he survived
the camp at Buchenwald,</i>

2387
03:13:37,750 --> 03:13:41,583
<i>as did his late wife,
and myself, in Dachau.</i>

2388
03:13:41,667 --> 03:13:43,875
<i>His first American
masterpiece,</i>

2389
03:13:43,958 --> 03:13:47,292
<i>the Van Buren Institute
outside of Philadelphia,</i>

2390
03:13:47,375 --> 03:13:50,833
<i>remained unfinished
until 1973.</i>

2391
03:13:50,917 --> 03:13:54,542
<i>The building referenced
his time at Buchenwald,</i>

2392
03:13:54,625 --> 03:13:59,167
<i>as well as the deeply felt
absence of his wife,</i>

2393
03:13:59,250 --> 03:14:01,667
<i>my aunt, Erzsébet.</i>

2394
03:14:02,458 --> 03:14:04,083
<i>For this project,</i>

2395
03:14:04,167 --> 03:14:08,375
<i>he re-imagined the camp's
claustrophobic interior cells</i>

2396
03:14:08,458 --> 03:14:10,750
<i>with precisely
the same dimensions</i>

2397
03:14:10,833 --> 03:14:13,583
<i>as his own place
of imprisonment,</i>

2398
03:14:13,667 --> 03:14:16,750
<i>save for one
electrifying exception.</i>

2399
03:14:18,375 --> 03:14:21,792
<i>When visitors looked
20 meters upwards,</i>

2400
03:14:21,875 --> 03:14:25,375
<i>the dramatic heights
of the glass roof above them</i>

2401
03:14:25,458 --> 03:14:28,625
<i>invited free thought,
freedom of identity.</i>

2402
03:14:28,708 --> 03:14:31,667
He further re-imagined
Buchenwald

2403
03:14:31,750 --> 03:14:35,833
and his wife's venue
of imprisonment, Dachau,

2404
03:14:35,917 --> 03:14:37,667
on the same grounds,

2405
03:14:39,167 --> 03:14:42,000
connected by a myriad
of secret corridors,

2406
03:14:42,083 --> 03:14:46,958
re-writing their history,
transcending space and time,

2407
03:14:47,042 --> 03:14:50,250
so that he and Erzsébet
would never be apart again.

2408
03:14:52,458 --> 03:14:53,708
Uncle...

2409
03:14:55,167 --> 03:14:57,750
you and Aunt Erzsébet
once spoke for me.

2410
03:14:57,833 --> 03:15:01,792
I speak for you now,
and am honored.

2411
03:15:01,875 --> 03:15:05,042
"Don't let anyone fool you,
Zsófia," he would say to me

2412
03:15:05,125 --> 03:15:09,375
as a struggling young mother
raising my daughter

2413
03:15:09,458 --> 03:15:12,000
during our first years
in Jerusalem.

2414
03:15:13,083 --> 03:15:16,000
"No matter what the others
try and sell you,

2415
03:15:17,417 --> 03:15:21,625
It is the destination,
not the journey."

